distraction: No; just trying to memorize as much as possible.
strategies: I basically thought of short phrases for connections - for example; things like \fish on a ferris wheel;\ for Olympia and Santa Monica; \potato in a pool\ for Hot Springs and Boise; \skiing on a train\ for Decatur and Boulder; \football in the fall\ for Syracuse and Ann Arbor... etc. I definitely could have been more specific since eventually many of the phrases blurred in my head trying to remember.
easier: Yes; I suppose the routes like above where the short phrases managed to stick in my head - it helped a lot if the letters were the same. For example; \fish on a ferris wheel\ stuck in my mind because there are two Fs.
comments: I would have preferred looking at a screen with ALL connections listed at once and only getting a certain amount of time to memorize those. I honestly think it was more difficult trying to remember connections that only flashed on the screen; along with making sure I pressed the 1 or 2 for the blue or yellow cross. Having that portion taken away would have helped me concentrate more on the airline connections. Thanks for the opportunity!
